Question: Android Socket programming: :I'm trying to implement a simple chat application. I have a server and a client. The server sends a message to the client and the client receives it. However, the client is not receiving the message. Here is my code: Server:
public class Server {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {
        ServerSocket serverSocket = new ServerSocket(1234);
        System.out.println("Waiting for client on port " + serverSocket.getLocalPort() + "...");

        Socket socket = serverSocket.accept();
        System.out.println("Connected to " + socket.getRemoteSocketAddress());

        DataOutputStream dataOutputStream = new DataOutputStream(socket.getOutputStream());
        dataOutputStream.writeUTF("Hello from Server!");
        dataOutputStream.close();
        socket.close();
    }
}

Client:
public class Client {
    public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {
        Socket socket = new Socket("localhost", 1234);
        System.out.println("Connected to " + socket.getRemoteSocketAddress());

        DataInputStream dataInputStream = new DataInputStream(socket.getInputStream());
        System.out.println(dataInputStream.readUTF());
        dataInputStream.close();
        socket.close();
    }
}

I have tried running the server and client on the same machine and on different machines, but I still can't receive the message. What could be the problem?
Answer:<<<api>>>: Socket.getInputStream
<<<code>>>: DataInputStream dataInputStream = new DataInputStream(socket.getInputStream());
String message = dataInputStream.readUTF();
<<<explanation>>>: You are using DataInputStream to read from the input stream of the socket. The readUTF() method reads a string from the socket. Make sure that the server is sending a string using the writeUTF() method.
